5:
How do you like your new
equipment, Vyron? No complaints, I
wager?
9:
Not bad at all. Though... it's kinda
flashy for my tastes.
15:
What do you mean? I think it's
simply astounding, the very picture
of a regal knight!
18:
I'd heard of how skilled you were,
Vyron. I suppose that's the famous
Single Strike Style of House Oinas?
22:
Nah. You'd be wrong there. I can't
use that style to save my damn life.
25:
I mean, think about it. If I were a
proper swordsman, I wouldn't need
to rely on projectiles and bombs,
would I?
28:
Anyone actually trained in the Oinas
style would have a heart attack if
they saw how I fight, heh.
32:
So... wait, I get it! You mix magic with
your sword fighting, kind of like the
way Nouins do it!
36:
Pretty high-spirited for a prince,
aren'tcha? Nialas sure has some
oddballs...
41:
There are those in other Houses who
say that Nouin-style fighting is too
unorthodox as well.
44:
I should add, this equipment was
prepared by a friend of mine. I, too,
find it bewildering.
48:
Heh. Just let an old man cling to his
sword and die in peace, would ya?
54:
You hear that I'm the Traitor of Oinas
and... you're just gonna go with it?
58:
I am the one who asked for your
entry into the Swallow Knights.
61:
I know full well the power you wield.
Without your sword, we would never
stand a chance.
63:
...Though I had not heard of the
assassination incident, Alk and Sir
Light informed me of your true
identity, Velgar Oinas.
67: And you've still got no doubts?
71:
Stella has already vouched for your
character.
75:
I gotta say... You people put waaaay
too much faith in that girl.
79:
There are few who could put up a
facade under her gaze.
83:
Why's that? Does she have magical
eyes like the ones I have heard talk
about?
87:
Naaaah, nothing like that. You know
how it is, just... whatever, those kinda
eyes!
90:
Well, believe what ya want. It's not
gonna change how I behave... Got it?
96:
Drinking all alone the night before
battle... How sad can you get?
99:
Pass me a bottle, old man. I'll take a
swig with you.
103:
Oh, it's you... Hah! Checking up on
me or somethin'?
108:
Like hell I am. A guy like me can't get
a drink in this place. It's so stifling.
112:
Hah! Compared to Palpebra, this
backwater country's just an
insignificant speck.
119:
Didn't think you'd be the type to run
off. You got caught off guard, huh?
127:
That Marden guy really made a
puppet out of you. That was some
show.
132:
Shut yer damn mouth! Things still
worked out, didn't they?
138:
How'd we end up sitting around
having a drink together?
145:
More so for me, since I met everyone
thirty years before you did.
149:
...Luck, huh? Guess there's some
truth to that...
152:
So, tomorrow's the big fight against
them monsters... Sorry, but I'll be
slippin' out to take care of some
business.
156:
Do whatever you want. I guess I'll
have to cover your ass.
160:
What was that? You're faaar too
young to talk to me that way!
167:
Tch... It's like being swarmed by a
buncha ants!
170:
The kingdom's on the brink. This is
no time to fool around...
173:
Heh... Guess I'm honor-bound to
spout that kinda line...
181: You ARE Velgar Oinas, aren't you?
191: My name is Marden. Marden Oxtan.
194:
That's right. I'm from the House of
Oxtan, which has ties with those
Kweturs lying on the ground.
198:
And yet... it doesn't seem like yer
here to finish me off.
202:
Don't be absurd. I'm a priest, so
violence isn't my style.
205:
I heard there was someone sniffing
around for information on Orgus
Oxtan. I'm just here to talk.
209:
Some holy man from Oxtan knows
me as the Traitor of Oinas? What's
really going on here?
216:
I believe we can be of use to each
other. How about it, Velgar?
222:
He had such a dark look in those
eyes. He got me...
225:
Damn... I've got no excuse for just
chasin' around some brat.
231:
So, in the end, what is it that ya
wanted?
